directions: In blender, process all ingredients until smooth. Serve immediately in tall glasses and garnish, if desired, with fresh strawberries.

title: french fry seasoning mix
directions: MIx together all ingredients. Sprinkle over hot French fries and season.

title: almond chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Melt the chocolate chips over a double boiler.
Place the flour and the cocoa on a work surface (or in a bowl), place the egg, sugar, butter, a pinch of salt, and a couple of drops of vanilla in the center.
Combine the ingredients well into a dough with a uniform consistency.
Add the chocolate and the almonds.
Use a spoon to scoop out small round shapes (the shapes will be irregular) and place the cookies on a baking sheet which has been buttered and floured or lined with parchment paper.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet campari tomatoes with basil and salty parmesan cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Slice top off of tomatoes and scoop out insides with melon baller.
Crush croutons and mix with cheese and basil.
Stuff tomatoes and bake for 10 minutes until cheese melts.
Do not bake too long or tomatoes will lose their shape.

title: ricotta sausage triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Cook sausage and onion in large skillet over MEDIUM-HIGH heat 8-10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently; drain.
Combine ricotta cheese, spinach and grated cheese in large bowl. Add sausage mixture, red peppers, olives, egg and seasonings; mix well.

Unroll phyllo dough; place 1 sheet on work surface with 1 short side nearest you. Spray with cooking spray; cut into 4 lengthwise strips. Cover remaining phyllo sheets with plastic wrap, then a damp towel until ready to use.

Place 1 generous tablespoon spinach mixture near 1 corner of 1 pastry strip. Fold corner of dough over filling to form triangle. Continue folding strip like a flag to make a triangle that completely encloses filling. Place, seam-side down, on baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining phyllo sheets. Spray with cooking spray
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: olive oil, spelt and orange loaf cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 160C.
Grease a loaf tin and set aside.
Beat the eggs in a large bowl.
Add the olive oil, orange peel, buttermilk (or milk), and sugar, and mix well.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt over the mixture and gently mix all the ingredients together until smooth.
Pour the mixture into a loaf tin and bake for 50-55 minutes or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. (If the loaf appears to brown too quickly, cover with aluminum foil.)
This cake will keep fresh and moist for up to 5 days if stored in a metal container or storage bag.

title: beetroot hummus
directions: Place all ingredients except salt and pepper into a bowl. Blend until the mixture reaches the desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon drop cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 10-inch Bundt pan; set aside.

Beat cake mix, pudding mix, I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!(R) made with Olive Oil Spread, 1/4 cup lemon juice, milk, eggs and lemon peel in large mixing bowl with electric mixer on low speed 30 seconds. Increase speed to medium and beat, scraping sides occasionally, 2 minutes or until blended. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes on wire rack; remove from pan and cool completely.
Meanwhile, cook 1/2 cup lemon juice with granulated sugar in 2-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Cool slightly, then evenly pour over cake.
Blend confectioners sugar with remaining 1/4 cup lemon juice in medium bowl for glaze; drizzle over cake.

title: mashed yams sims style
directions: Pre-heat the oven to 375.
With a fork puncture the yams with a couple of fork pokes. I would lay a small sheet of aluminum foil under neath as juices will bake out. Roast the yams for about 45 minutes.
If you like roasted garlic too - you can roast the garlic for about 20 minutes.
Remove them from the oven and let them cool off slightly. You can put them in the fridge to speed up the process. When they are cool enough to handle - cut them in half and scoop out the good stuff.
With a potato masher, mash up the yams. Add the garlic, kosher salt and pepper and the cream cheese. Mix it all together and serve.
The cream texture of the yams and the roasted flavour are divine.

title: breakfast bruschetta
directions: This dish gets you out of the norm of the generic eggs and toast breakfast.
The recipe is for 2 people and can be multiplied easily (you may not need to increase the amount of garlic).
First mix your ricotta by adding a pinch of salt and pepper and olive oil.
Then toast your bread.
While the bread is toasting make your scrambled eggs.
For soft (not rubbery) eggs, cook them slowly in the pan on low heat.
To start, melt some butter in a small non-stick skillet.
Crack the eggs into a separate bowl (to avoid any bits of shell) and whisk.
Add a pinch of salt and pepper.
Pour into the p

title: vanilla extract
directions: Slice vanilla beans length wise. Place in a sealable jar.
Pour vodka into the jar, seal and shake.
Place jar in a cool dark place and shake once every few days for about a month. The longer you let it sit, the better the vanilla extract will be.

title: michelada
directions: Salt the rim of a tall glass.
Squeeze in the juice of half to a whole large lime; add a dash of Tabasco sauce and the Worcestershire sauce.
Pour in beer and gently mix.

title: griddled chili wings
directions: Mix all ingredients but chicken wings. Add in wings and mix well. Refrigerate for about 1 hour.

Preheat indoor grill over medium-high heat and make sure your kitchen is well ventilated. Place wings on griddle, turning every 1 1/2 minutes, getting a good charred crust all around and preventing burns. Total cook time is about 12 minutes or until internal temperature is 165°.
Serve with you favorite cool blue cheese dip!

title: peach and nectarine dessert
directions: Preheat the oven to 160 C/300 F/gas mark 2.

Make a small incision in the top of each peach, place them on a little ovenproof tray and top each with a little of the buter. Sprinkle the fructose over them then roast in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.
For the nectarines saute them for 2 minutes in the butter, add the Amaretto, the sugar and the water then reboil. Set aside.
Make sugar cages by making a caramel with the sugar and fructose then shape over the back of a ladle which you will have greased with some groundnut oil. Remove them as they harden slightly.
To serve, place the nectarines in the bottom of 4 plates followed by a spoonful of the mascarpone, then a sugar cage followed by a peach, a sprig of mint then another sugar cage.

title: crostini with whipped ricotta & artichoke olive tapenade
directions: To a food processor, add the artichoke hearts, the marinading liquid, olives, garlic cloves and a handful of fresh parsley.
Pulse until a fine course consistency. Do not puree it, a little texture is good! Set aside.
In a bowl add the ricotta, whipping cream and season with the salt and some pepper. Whip using a hand mixer for approx 1.5 minutes, until light and creamy.
To assemble simply put a dollop of the whipped ricotta on the crostini and then top that with a bit of the tapenade. So much flavor in each bite!

title: chicken kebabs
directions: Cut up your chicken into small pieces, this can be plain or marinated in a sauce
Next cut up some pepper, mushrooms and onion into small chunks
Put your prepared chicken and vegetables onto a skewer and cook in the oven or on a BQQ
